WEBVTT

00:11.970 --> 00:14.014
[subway tracks rattling]

00:21.021 --> 00:24.774
[dramatic instrumental music playing]

00:27.777 --> 00:28.611
[man chuckles]

00:41.666 --> 00:43.710
[woman giggles]

00:59.517 --> 01:00.643
[in Korean] Are you okay?

01:00.727 --> 01:01.603
Uh-huh.

01:03.855 --> 01:05.356
[woman gasps]

01:05.440 --> 01:07.108
[breathing rapidly]

01:07.192 --> 01:08.485
Your stomach! Somebody help!

01:08.568 --> 01:09.986
[screaming]

01:10.070 --> 01:12.989
[all speaking in Korean]

01:13.073 --> 01:14.032
[screaming]

01:14.699 --> 01:16.451
[wails in pain]

01:16.534 --> 01:18.161
[flesh tearing]

01:18.244 --> 01:20.747
[woman screaming]

01:20.830 --> 01:22.749
[squelching]

01:22.832 --> 01:25.877
[baby gasps for air, cries]

01:25.960 --> 01:29.881
[Pogo] On the 12th hour
of the first day of October 1989,

01:29.964 --> 01:33.384
16 women around the world gave birth.

01:33.468 --> 01:35.553
This was unusual only in the fact

01:35.637 --> 01:39.933
that none of these women had been pregnant
when the day first began.

01:44.562 --> 01:48.566
Sir Reginald Hargreeves,
eccentric billionaire and adventurer,

01:48.650 --> 01:52.862
resolved to locate and adopt
as many of the children as possible.

01:52.946 --> 01:54.114
Extraordinary.

01:54.697 --> 01:55.615
[thunderclap]

01:56.282 --> 01:57.408
[baby mewls]

01:57.492 --> 02:00.286
How much do you want for it?
Surely you don't want to keep it.

02:00.370 --> 02:02.038
[in Korean] How much do you want for him?

02:02.122 --> 02:04.999
[in English] You lay one finger
on my grandson, I slice you in half!

02:05.083 --> 02:08.253
Excellent! I like a spirited negotiator.

02:08.336 --> 02:10.755
[thunder rumbling]

02:10.839 --> 02:12.465
[school bell rings]

02:12.549 --> 02:16.261
["Sometimes" by Gerry Cinnamon playing]

02:28.356 --> 02:31.484
♪ Sometimes, just sometimes ♪

02:31.568 --> 02:33.987
♪ Maybe more than some of the time ♪

02:34.070 --> 02:36.114
♪ I'm on a false ego trip ♪

02:36.197 --> 02:37.949
♪ Insecurity is rife ♪

02:38.032 --> 02:40.743
♪ I'm not the ideal person
To be lecturing on life ♪

02:40.827 --> 02:42.537
♪ But if you wanna know ♪

02:43.121 --> 02:44.998
♪ Some things I've learned about myself ♪

02:45.081 --> 02:48.126
♪ Being in sticky situations
I won't bore you with the filth ♪

02:48.209 --> 02:51.337
♪ Breaking bones and sniffing gear
Pouring blood and sweat and tears ♪

02:51.421 --> 02:52.922
-[grunts]
-♪ In a nutshell, I suppose ♪

02:53.006 --> 02:55.967
♪ It's the way the water flows ♪

02:58.970 --> 03:02.265
♪ Yeah, that's the way the story goes ♪

03:02.348 --> 03:05.143
[crowd cheering]

03:05.226 --> 03:06.811
[woman in crowd] Love you, Marcus!

03:06.895 --> 03:09.522
♪ Sometimes, just sometimes ♪

03:09.606 --> 03:10.481
♪ Well, all right ♪

03:10.565 --> 03:12.275
-♪ Maybe all of the time ♪
-[raven cawing]

03:12.358 --> 03:14.319
♪ I'm on a false ego trip ♪

03:14.402 --> 03:16.362
♪ Well, I'm a renegade of sorts ♪

03:16.446 --> 03:19.115
♪ I roam the concrete jungle
Hunting idiots for sport ♪

03:19.199 --> 03:21.492
-♪ And now the cocaine scene ♪
-[caws]

03:21.576 --> 03:23.286
♪ It picked me up and made me frown ♪

03:23.369 --> 03:26.164
♪ That's when joking says
That music helps the medicine go down ♪

03:26.247 --> 03:28.124
♪ Hey, it makes you feel alive ♪

03:28.208 --> 03:29.751
♪ More like demons of the night ♪

03:29.834 --> 03:31.377
♪ Flinging powder up your nose ♪

03:31.461 --> 03:33.963
♪ It's the way the water flows… ♪

03:34.547 --> 03:37.175
[cube speaks]

03:37.258 --> 03:40.136
Hey, next round's on Christopher!

03:40.220 --> 03:41.554
[patrons cheering]

03:41.638 --> 03:43.640
[Christopher speaks]

03:45.350 --> 03:47.769
[man] I said no pepperoni.
No pepperoni, dumbass!

03:47.852 --> 03:50.063
-You said no mushrooms.
-[mocking] I speak English!

03:50.146 --> 03:51.356
So does my son.

03:51.439 --> 03:53.358
We speak American, asshole.

03:53.441 --> 03:55.652
You are an American asshole.

03:55.735 --> 03:57.528
[store owner] Let go of me! Let go!

03:57.612 --> 03:59.822
Get outta my store! Get out of here!

03:59.906 --> 04:03.493
♪ Don't look the same for you and me
Drinking cider in a golf course ♪

04:03.576 --> 04:06.579
♪ Just a distant memory
Down the park and pick a fight ♪

04:06.663 --> 04:11.167
♪ Popping pills all through the night
That's the way the water flows ♪

04:11.876 --> 04:12.710
[man groans]

04:14.629 --> 04:17.340
♪ Yeah, that's the way the story goes ♪

04:17.423 --> 04:18.424
This better be pepperoni.

04:20.051 --> 04:22.303
♪ Sometimes ♪

04:26.766 --> 04:28.643
♪ Sometimes ♪

04:28.726 --> 04:32.897
[alarm blaring]

04:32.981 --> 04:36.276
♪ Just sometimes ♪

04:39.404 --> 04:41.864
♪ Just sometimes ♪

04:41.948 --> 04:43.157
[alarm continues]

04:43.241 --> 04:44.659
[Reginald] This isn't your home.

04:44.742 --> 04:47.287
[Allison] What are you talking about?
This is the Umbrella Academy.

04:47.370 --> 04:48.454
[Reginald] Wrong again.

04:48.538 --> 04:51.165
This… is the Sparrow Academy.

05:02.510 --> 05:04.512
Dad, who the hell are these assholes?

05:06.014 --> 05:07.223
[Umbrellas] Shit.

05:07.724 --> 05:08.850
Ben.

05:12.520 --> 05:13.646
Is that really you?

05:14.522 --> 05:17.692
And who are the weirdos on the balcony?

05:18.276 --> 05:20.153
[Reginald] They are the Sparrows.

05:21.029 --> 05:22.155
My children.

05:22.238 --> 05:24.824
[rumbling]

05:26.534 --> 05:29.078
[dramatic orchestral music playing]

05:31.080 --> 05:32.665
[energy twinkling]

05:41.674 --> 05:42.884
[electricity crackling]

05:57.148 --> 05:59.734
I'm sorry.
What do you mean, your children?

06:00.234 --> 06:01.736
That's not possible, old man.

06:01.819 --> 06:04.989
[Reginald] Of course it is!
I think I'd know, wouldn't I?

06:05.656 --> 06:07.867
Everybody else can see Ben, right?

06:07.950 --> 06:09.160
Cute hat, Sundance.

06:09.243 --> 06:12.622
[Reginald] They call themselves
the Umbrella Academy,

06:13.206 --> 06:16.209
a group of scheming,
perfidious malcontents

06:16.292 --> 06:18.503
who accosted me in the fall of 1963

06:18.586 --> 06:20.922
when I was away on business in Dallas.

06:21.005 --> 06:24.092
Be warned, they claim to be my spawn.

06:25.343 --> 06:28.012
Claim? Look, Five,
what the hell is going on?

06:28.096 --> 06:30.056
I don't know yet, but it's concerning.

06:30.139 --> 06:32.934
-Is he telling the truth?
-Not the part about us being perfidious.

06:33.017 --> 06:35.478
No, we're amateur-fidious, at best.

06:35.561 --> 06:38.356
But we are his children.
This is our house.

06:38.439 --> 06:40.691
Yeah, yeah. We, uh… We grew up here.

06:40.775 --> 06:42.568
-[mocking] "Yeah, we grew up here."
-[snickers]

06:42.652 --> 06:45.029
I kind of think we would have noticed you.

06:46.155 --> 06:48.449
Hi. I'm Luther.

06:49.283 --> 06:50.993
Okay. None of you belong here.

06:51.077 --> 06:51.994
[Fei] Oh! Well, then.

06:52.078 --> 06:54.831
I guess we'll just pack our bags
and move out.

06:54.914 --> 06:57.959
[Christopher speaks]

06:58.543 --> 07:00.670
-[Sparrows chuckling]
-You slay me, Chris.

07:04.048 --> 07:06.384
I wasn't expecting company. [sighs]

07:06.467 --> 07:08.469
This is the best I could do on short--

07:08.553 --> 07:10.763
[in robotic voice] Short… Short notice.

07:12.056 --> 07:12.890
Mom.

07:12.974 --> 07:15.143
Mom? She's a robot, you perv.

07:15.226 --> 07:17.145
-It's not a robot.
-Hey, don't you call him that.

07:17.228 --> 07:18.813
-Or what?
-Come closer and find out.

07:18.896 --> 07:20.690
-Luther! Guys, chill!
-[Ben] Think I'm afraid?

07:20.773 --> 07:23.067
-Stand down, Ben.
-Look at that! She's got a voice!

07:23.151 --> 07:25.403
How about I hide
that big Rubik's Cube up your ass?

07:25.486 --> 07:26.779
-Enough!
-[hissing]

07:28.364 --> 07:30.324
[Marcus] I don't know what circus
you escaped from

07:30.408 --> 07:32.034
or how you got past our security,

07:32.118 --> 07:33.119
but we're done here.

07:33.202 --> 07:35.413
You got 30 seconds
to get out of our house.

07:35.496 --> 07:36.831
And if we don't?

07:37.832 --> 07:40.001
Then we'll have to settle this
the old-fashioned way.

07:40.084 --> 07:42.879
[ominous orchestral music playing]

07:43.796 --> 07:44.881
Agreed.

07:48.384 --> 07:49.844
[neck cracks]

07:49.927 --> 07:53.639
[ominous music swells]

07:54.849 --> 07:56.893
["Footloose" by Kenny Loggins playing]

08:14.410 --> 08:17.288
♪ I been working so hard ♪

08:17.371 --> 08:20.291
-Get him, Luther!
-♪ Keep punching my card ♪

08:20.374 --> 08:22.668
-♪ Eight hours, for what? ♪
-Luther, what are you doing?

08:23.169 --> 08:24.795
Protecting our honor, bro.

08:25.922 --> 08:28.216
♪ I got this feeling ♪

08:28.299 --> 08:31.844
♪ That time's just holding me down ♪

08:33.763 --> 08:36.098
Oh shit! We're really good at this!

08:36.933 --> 08:39.227
♪ I'll hit the ceiling ♪

08:40.019 --> 08:43.231
♪ Or else I'll tear up this town ♪

08:46.609 --> 08:48.194
